			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=26609'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/warrior.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=12141#M12141">51</a> of 332
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 456 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I'm <U>not</U> absolutely sure of my facts here, but I picked this up somewhere regarding design choices since GoD post adjustment.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Knights sugested to developers that one of the problems/concerns they had with Defensive is that it confered a kind of gear indenpendent advantage to Warriors. Their concern (and here's where I'm not positive about my facts) was that comparasons were made between simularly geared Warriors and Knights. Yet, if you look in Magelo you will discover that Warriors in general tend to be better equipped than Knights. Therefore (still not positive&nbsp;about my facts here) it was more appropriate to concider comparasons in tiers, particularly where average Knights compared in fact to Warriors, not how they compared based on what they COULD achieve.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think that's the essence of your argument too sir.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>I believe the developers bought on to this argument and as a result, the vast majority of single group content is designed so it is doable by average players&nbsp;based on what they have actually achieved.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></DIV>But look at it this way for a moment. Spells, disciplines, levels, AA's, etc. ALL function to provide largely gear independent abilities to classes. My twink Paladin made level 66 and with relatively ZERO effort obtained a simply awesome aggro spell (for example). If you can find blue con moss snakes to kill (and that's pretty much what I did) and can come up with 8kpp in echange for that minimal effort and achievement you (if you were a Paladin) could be using that spell as well.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So with a whole LOT of non-achievement acquired character improvement from spells, disciplines, and just plain leveling...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>where does&nbsp;<U>achievement</U> come into play in a <U>character progression</U> fantasy role playing game?? In console games it's twitch reflexes and sub-concious reaction to learned attack and responce pattern. But EQ is not a console game sir. Nor is it about killing 100,000 moss snakes nor doing 100,000 trade skill combines......</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's risk/reward.&nbsp;As a hardcore raider, that's&nbsp;&nbsp;months to learn the flag encounters, beat them, and get everyone flaged. Perhaps more months before the first piece of loot anyone wants drops. Do the math. 52x5hours = 1 raid = 250 man hours. A <U>single raid</U> equals the effort of a casual player putting in months of personal effort - often with NOTHING to show for it except negative experiance.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The risk sir is monumental. The rewards are hardly in line with the risk, but SoE can't make sucessful hardcore raiders into the demi-gods they probably deserve to be.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As a result, 100 or 200&nbsp;more AC,&nbsp;a HUGE difference in gear, has a benefit of reducing damage by 5-10%. Not only is the gear reasonably close in stats, the difference does NOT confer as much advantage as one might suppose. Our spells, disciplines, etc. confer a lot of gear independent ability, surely differences in gear obtained through achievement should as well - this <U>is</U> a character <U>advancement</U> based game, neh??</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>10-23-2005</span> <span class=time_text>07:07 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
