		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I would have to agree with BB on the risk/reward thing...heaven forbid. There is no single group adventure or location that will entail the same kinda risk that the high end raid does. It is not possible, not even high end raiders could fight through mobs like that as a single group.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I do understand Olav though in respect to the average. It does prove difficult to make a game where you have zones challangeing to both groups. The instance zones I think are part of the solution. Flags used to be, if you weren't good enough to get the flag you didn't get in. If you aren't the right level you don't get in either. They seem biased against casuals, but casuals would have a hard time fighting in zones designed for high end raiders.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Look at those pre season collage football games where teams like Florida State play some dinky class 2 school. The outcome is useually 70 to 7. That doesn't mean the 2A school is bad, just majorly outclassed. That's why there are divisions in football, to allow more balanced and fair playing fields. The division 3 national champ is as much a national champ as the division 1 school because they were the best in thier challange rateing.</DIV>	
