			>
			<DIV>I'm personally glad there's a large gap between casuals and raiders.&nbsp; It gives me something to strive for.&nbsp; Honestly, if I could close the gap too well on my own, it would not just destroy the feeling of an <STRONG>MM</STRONG>orpg, but I'd get bored way too fast.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I like the "/drool factor"... and today, I wield things that I at one point I thought I'd never have...&nbsp; Think about what a fully Anguish geared player (most likely a small amount of actual players) really has to desire, what's left for them to strive for...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The day I have nothing left to /drool over... is the day I stop playing EQ...</DIV>
