		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Typically in the past I have felt the gap to be too large.&nbsp; Of late however, I do not feel this way.&nbsp; I think there are some cases though that force the non-raider out of their comfort zone, where they don't see the continual string of success and think that the gap is the sole problem.&nbsp; This tends to leads to attitudes like the one Frodlin mentioned earlier.&nbsp; I don't really think there is a fix for that, because at the end of the day it is an attitude, and not something that can be coded into the game.&nbsp; There is a slippery slope you risk crossing if you narrow the gap too much, because at what point is it enough?&nbsp; At what point to you say ok the difference is where it should be, I can guarantee that ANY gap will have it's share of complaints, but a gap should exist none the less.&nbsp; I don't exactly agree with Frodlin that the 50% policy has been ever present in EQ.&nbsp; It seems to go more in spirts.&nbsp; Where we will go for a couple of expansions where the gap is larger than that, then an expansion or two where it gets back to that par or even narrows the gap a bit.&nbsp; If it were more steady it probably wouldn't be as noticeable.&nbsp; When I think back to original EQ, Kunark and even velious, the gap did not appear that large.&nbsp; With the release of Luclin and PoP it appeared to grow much greater.&nbsp; LDoN aleviated some of that, while LoY didn't do much, and GoD seemed to keep the status quo.&nbsp; OoW, and DoN seemed to narrow it back down to Velious levels imo.&nbsp; DoD hasn't really changed that from what I have seen so far, but then I haven't seen too many raid loot links yet.&nbsp; The gap as it is now is probably the closest to healthy it has been in quite some time I don't think much tweaking is necessary from a loot standpoint.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Something I think some non-raiders miss when they look at how many months it takes a raider to acquire gear is it isn't the number of months it takes, it is the hours spent working towards that upgrade.&nbsp; Based on what I have seen some raiders post, it can be 2-5 months between upgrades (raiding 5 nights a week for 4-6 hours per night).&nbsp; As a non-raider I have also gone 2-5 months without an upgrade in gear, and that is playing 4 hours a night and a good 8-10 hours on weekends, and seems fairly reasonable to me.&nbsp; But if as a non-raider you only get in about 4 hours a week, then 2-5 months should not only be acceptable, but should be considered lucky.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now something else that seems to get over looked in all of these discussions is the massive overgeneralization when using terms such as hard-core and casual.&nbsp; There are so many different categories of raider and non-raider it isn't even funny.&nbsp; The types of players in EQ can not be divided up so simply, and thus balancing content around gear of the many tiers of player and play styles is daunting.&nbsp; And if you take the extremes of both the raider and non-raider the gap will look huge, and in those cases it should.&nbsp; The most casual of non-raider should have far inferior gear to the most hard core raider.&nbsp; The narrow gap should be between the Hardcore non-raider and the casual raider...and the gap there is actually quite narrow.&nbsp; The key difference is the hardcore non-raider will get out of their easy kill groups and do the tougher content to close that gap with the casual raider.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But so long as we only categorize players as casual and raider it will always appear that the gap is too large.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>To sum up, if I can from my own ramblings, the gap when looking at the full spectrum of playstyles is actually quite in line compared to a few times in the past.&nbsp; There are some exceptions to this, but not many.&nbsp;&nbsp; I would just hope that SOE keeps this as the satus quo, and continues down this path, instead of widening the gap back up in the future, which I haven't seen anyone ask for.&nbsp; I don't think the gap needs to be narrowed at this point.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<img src=" http://mywebpages.comcast.net/lunrak/LunrakSOESig.gif"><br><A href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1125375">Lunrak of Fennin Ro</A><br><br>If you have to tell me how uber you are...then you aren't. <br>If you are uber I will already know, and wont need you to remind me.
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
