		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Hmmm...&nbsp;&nbsp; I think the issue of gear&nbsp; Casual vs. Raid, etc, although Lunrak has a HUGE point, does seem to get bigger, it would have to seem that way if the 50% rule or whatever you call it is an actuality. I'm gona do a Shar type comparison of what one might be trying to say. We all have parents, or elder's, etc. As we age, we narrow the gab between them in a percent... Let's say I am 20 and my Mother is 40, twice my age. BUt when I am 40, she will be 60, and I will be 60% her age. Turn me into the Casual, and my Mother into the Raider, and I think this is something of what is being asked, or at least as close of a picture I can come up with.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>BB, not every casual is lazy, or a bad player. I know you've ran accross some great Casual player's in your time, there's no way you could have gone that long and not seen them. As I'm sure you have been around some BAD playing Raider's.&nbsp; I have, for sure, and vice versa. Although alot of Casual players could get to the top, it would mean leaving friends in their guild, and in alot of cases.........Family&nbsp; that plays with them. I'm one of them type's, and the only way I'm gonna ever advance, is through the guild I'm in, cuz that's where my son made his home. I don't feel lazy, I feel like I'm being a Cool Mom at times, but never feel lazy. I have a desire to join one of the guild's that some of my in game friends left for, but I live with my son, he's my world. It's not fair to categorize like that. I know you weren't talking specifically about anyone, but you generalized casuals. Most the people in my guild are the one's I grouped with when I just started playing with my son. Befriending us when trying to kill orc camps, first time we ventured out into the commons and found Befallen, and went into LSM and walked around the Temple (Still trying to fix faction for some of our first toons that don't get much play, now). It's not about being lazy sometimes, but about who you enjoy playing with. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm not sure where the gap should lie, but I do know their has to be a gap. And alot of times it don't look like it's a 50% better then, but more like 100% better. A bp that does 75AC is only half as good as one that does 150AC, not 50% better, but 100% better. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I do think at times it's closer, and other times wider. Expansions seem to have a hard time being 100% equal to what they are trying to add content for. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>XOX did get an alot&nbsp; more RAider's then Casuals in my view by the way. I didn't see any casual guilds getting completely obliterated like I seen Raid guilds', of which at least 25% of dont' even exist anymore, at least on my server, yet hardly any casual guilds had that type of loss.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
