		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>The real test Jazzy is, am <U>I</U> having fun.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you log on night after night for a couple of hours and spend most of your evening /lfg - that's not fun. If your never get an upgrade, that's not fun. Etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The designers/developers have tried&nbsp;to make it entertaining, but a lot of that is solely up to you. Yes, yes... I understand that sometimes they get lost and think "challange" = fun, killing the same 16 mobs every 15 minutes = fun, etc. But they <U>are</U> trying.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Players have to try too. Being in a family guild, you can focus a bit more on the "fun" and a bit less on advancement. Remember, progress in EQ largely = the abiity to change the scenery - where you are fighting/nothing more. You geared up so you can fight in WoS, but WoS mobs hit harder, ad infinitum.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Instead of focusing on the fact that a Cloak of Regretful Transgressions (what I wear) may be forever out of the reach of you and your guildmates, notice that Loyalist Shield of Honor is likely <U>not</U> out of your reach and pretty darned uber.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Players in lower&nbsp;tier guilds that can't get over the fact that they are just now breaking into PoTime and find that distressing and "casual" players that dwell on&nbsp;the fact that the ubers have 110AC BP's while the best they can acquire is a Grandmaster's BP are <U>not</U> going to enjoy the game.</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I realize that in a character advancement game progress means a lot. But I submit that if you are not enjoying the process and what you will be doing should you log in tonight, then you just&nbsp;might not log in. I suck therefore I MUST log in tonight will only take you so far.</DIV>	
