		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>"I realize that in a character advancement game progress means a lot. But I submit that if you are not enjoying the process and what you will be doing should you log in tonight, then you just&nbsp;might not log in. I suck therefore I MUST log in tonight will only take you so far."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This phrase says it all, though I might replace the part about sucking with 'I must progress...', but in any event, if a player ever gets to a point of feeling "I MUST log in", then I would suspect the game ceases to be fun, pretty quickly.&nbsp; At one point in my time in EQ I was logging in for the sole purpose of progressing, and fun be damned.&nbsp; It felt like a job.&nbsp; It got old fast, I burned out and left for a good 9 months.&nbsp; Now I was just trying to get levels, but you can burn yourself out trying to get that gear too.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Another argument that comes up alot is what is needed for the content you will face.&nbsp; I honestly don't know if DoN cultural will be enough for a lvl 70 non-raider to do MPG trials or hunt in RSS, I truely don't.&nbsp; I will find that out eventually (god I hate tradeskilling lol).&nbsp; And that is really all that is required of non-raid gear, that it allows us to continue to progress.&nbsp; As long as it doesn't force us to gimped along by 5 hardcore raiders to get our spells, discs, or gear, then it is sufficient.&nbsp; It must only allow us access to the content we need to progress.&nbsp; Sure, like others I druel at the 200 HP stats but then I think, what in the world would I need that for?&nbsp; You see I know where my friends like to hunt, and with one or two exceptions I only can think of one or two zones my friends want to hunt that it is counter productive to have me there as their tank.&nbsp; I might be able to when I gear up some more, and get a few more tanking AAs, but in the mean time most of my friends want to hunt in places I can pretty easily tank and am even bored with.&nbsp; </DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
