		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>When we try making these hypothetical could-happen magelos, can we try and stay in the realm of the realistic?&nbsp; I'd like it if we avoided slapping a 400K bazaar aug on every piece of 150K Cultural armor please.&nbsp; We're trying to discuss the difference between relatively casual and hard core raiding, and if the 50% gap is A) viable given the size of that 50% with today's HP/AC and mob DPS numbers and B)&nbsp; If it really is 50% after secondary stats are factored in.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Generating a Magelo toon for a character that would cost:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>~ 275K in Radiant/Ebon Crystals</DIV>
<DIV>~ 500K in Metallic Drake Scales alone assuming you make it yourself and never fail a combine</DIV>
<DIV>~1,000,000 plat for the augments assuming you buy them, do the cutting, and alchemy/poison crafting yourself, never fail AND get deals and never fail the subcombines.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And don't tell me you farmed the cyrstals or the TS parts, because for all the RS statue drops and MPG Trials, you've been busy in other content.&nbsp; Which may have gotten you a deal on aug drops, but that means you're spending even MORE time there given the one loot/ one rune rule most groups seem to follow, and you had to go in on a lot of non-usable loot to sell in order to pay off your 1.7 MILLION play debt for your buyables.&nbsp; Unless you generated your plat through unofficial and unapproved means- in which case it would have been more effective to "generate" your entire character through unofficial and unapproved means.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So with all that said, lets try and stick to the realm of likely, not possible on those magelos.&nbsp; LIKELY a relatively casual warrior will have one or two Trial drops.&nbsp; LIKELY he'll have one or two augs from RSS.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My main point is, with the gap expanding like it is, people who are friends in two different levels of progress in the game will find it difficult to play together as their characters, and that sholdn't happen.&nbsp; </DIV>	
		</td></tr>
