			<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Heimdall-RN wrote:<BR>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So with all that said, lets try and stick to the realm of likely, not possible on those magelos.&nbsp; LIKELY a relatively casual warrior will have one or two Trial drops.&nbsp; LIKELY he'll have one or two augs from RSS.<BR>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>It's also unlikely to find a player that is completely Anguish geared... I have NO trial drops, I have NO RS augs... you know what that means?&nbsp; That means I have plenty more work to do in order to efficiently tank MPG trials and RS to get my upgrades.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>With Shrouds and monster missions and all sorts of DoN and DoD tasks, you shouldn't be TOO hard pressed to group with anyone from any line of progression.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Personally, if you want to see the gap closed... go out and close it...&nbsp;it's a&nbsp;<STRONG><EM>fact</EM></STRONG> that you can come very close to some very high end gear without ever stepping foot into a raid zone that would need it.</DIV>
