		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Key to enjoying EQ is being able to progress through new content (new to you), and improve your character.&nbsp; Any time a player feels stagnant, the game is not enjoyable.&nbsp;&nbsp;This applies to&nbsp;raiders and non raiders.&nbsp; EQ is&nbsp;not about comparing your toon to another one.&nbsp; We all&nbsp;need to be doing&nbsp;a level of content that is chalenging, but doable by your character.&nbsp; Once you hit your desired level of gear, guess what? you will want more, we all do, so key is to have a path upward, and all players want this.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I do agree that there were certain levels that seemed more frustrating than others, and seemed to be hard to get past with few equipment upgrades available.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I disagree with the stats listed at the begining of the post,&nbsp;you can acheive much better without a single raid drop,&nbsp;and without huge amounts of plat farming or trade skills.&nbsp;&nbsp;Starting with LDON,&nbsp;then OOW, DON, and now DODH, EQ has provided&nbsp;a progresion path.&nbsp; Teir One OOW armor is nice, get full set (minus chest and legs),&nbsp;plus&nbsp;DON stuff,&nbsp;and single group drops, you can get past stats listed at begining of post.&nbsp; 10k unbuffed hp is acheivable with 1700 to 1800 ac.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Not going to touch the raider vs non raider debate.&nbsp;</DIV>	
